  "_comment": "Per-column binary storage layout for the ClickBench `hits` table. Each fixed-width column is a single mmap-able file of raw little-endian values. Each TEXT column is two files: <col>_off.bin (uint64 offsets, length n+1) and <col>_data.bin (concatenated UTF-8 bytes). Column files live under <gendb_dir>/hits/. EventDate is stored as int16 (days since 1970-01-01 fits — Yandex hits range is 2013-07-02..2013-07-31 ≈ 15890-15917) but we keep int32 for safety. EventTime/ClientEventTime/LocalEventTime stored as int32 (epoch seconds fits in uint32 until 2106; signed int32 is safer for arithmetic). HitColor is a single char stored as int8. SMALLINT columns stored as int16 — many are 0/1 bitmaps but we keep them honest. URLHash/RefererHash require int64.",
